verbose_text: XREF_BIBR The aim of this study was to investigate the impact of food ingestion on plasma levels of PS+ particles (using FC) and small EVs (using EV Array) in general and their TF bearing subtypes in particular as well as the effect of prandial state on levels of circulating TF antigen (Ag), TF activity, and procoagulant phospholipids (PPLs).
